<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 5:45AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IS IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT TONIGHT...
A widely scattered region of freezing rain has redeveloped and
will overspread across Midland and Bay County within the hour.
Temperatures now range between 30 to 33 degrees and will drop
slightly at the onset of precipitation. This will allow
precipitation to freeze on contact on untreated roadways and
surfaces. Drivers are urged to prepare for icy roads and
pedestrians should be prepared for icy paved surfaces.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
